GENTEXT/REMARKS/1. Appointments for Marines listed in paragraph 4a through 4.b.2 will be issued to fill vacancies in the selected grade in the assigned order of seniority. Monthly promotions will be announced by separate Marine Administrative Messages (MARADMIN).

2. Details specific to Professional Military Education (PME) requirements, applicable only to the FY24 Staff Sergeant (SSgt) Promotion Selection Board, are contained in paragraph 6 of this MARADMIN and should be read in detail as they depart from previous promotion board considerations.

3. In accordance with reference (c), Marines are not required to wait until their seniority number is reached each month to gain obligated service (OBS). Upon release of this MARADMIN any Marine selected for promotion by the FY24 SSgt Promotion Selection Board is authorized to submit, via the Total Force Retention System (TFRS),the necessary reenlistment or extension request to ensure they will have at least 24 months remaining on contract after the date of their promotion. Based off seniority number Marines should work with their Career Planner to gain OBS as soon as possible to avoid a delay in their promotion.

4. The following selectees were approved on 14 June 2024.
